'''Zen Pinball 2''' is a [[pinball]] video game developed by [[Zen Studios]] for the [[Wii U]], [[PlayStation 3]], [[PlayStation 4]], Android, and [[PlayStation Vita]].<ref>http://blog.zenstudios.com/press/press_archive/Zen_Pinball_2_Wii_U_Announcement.pdf</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Zen Pinball Official Website|url=http://www.zenpinball.com|publisher=Zen Studios|accessdate=10 April 2012}}</ref> The game was announced on April 9, 2012. The first PlayStation versions was released on September 4, 2012 in North America and September 5 in Europe<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2012-04-09-zen-pinball-2-announced-for-ps3-vita|title=Zen Pinball 2 announced for PS3, Vita|date=9 April 2012|work=Eurogamer.net|accessdate=9 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/5900579/zen-studios-brings-its-free-pinball-platform-to-the-playstation-3-and-ps-vita|title=Zen Studios Brings Its Free Pinball Platform to the PlayStation 3 and PS Vita|author=Mike Fahey|publisher=Gawker Media|work=Kotaku|accessdate=9 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.joystiq.com/2012/08/08/zen-pinball-2-on-ps3-vita-popcap-table-this-september/|title=Zen Pinball 2 on PS3/Vita, PopCap table this September|author=Alexander Sliwinski|work=Engadget|accessdate=9 August 2015}}</ref> while the Wii U version was released on March 21, 2013 in North America and January 31, 2013 in Europe.

''Zen Pinball 2'' is an upgrade to the original ''[[Zen Pinball|Zen Pinball (3D)]]''. It features a new UI and an upgraded version of the game engine which improves graphics and physics. There is also a new social sharing feature which allows players to post their scores on Facebook.

Although ''Zen Pinball 2'' is fundamentally a free download, users who already own ''Zen Pinball'' or ''[[Marvel Pinball]]'' for the PlayStation 3 are able to use all their [[downloadable content]] in the PS versions of ''Zen Pinball 2'', which imports automatically. There were 26 tables at launch (available separately as premium DLC) each of which are available as a free trial (though packs like ''Marvel Pinball: Vengeance'' and ''Virtue'' will still have to be bought as a whole). Users who purchase a pinball table on one Sony console are able to play it for free on the other.

==Features==
*''Zen Pinball 2'' is cross-platform entitled in the PlayStation versions. Any content bought are playable on both PlayStation 3 and PlayStation Vita at no extra charge.
*Free trials are available for each table so players can try each table before purchasing.
*Those who already own ''Zen Pinball'' or ''Marvel Pinball'' content are able to import their purchases into ''Zen Pinball 2'' for free, receiving graphics, physics and social system upgrades at no extra cost.
*''Zen Pinball 2'' launched with 26 different pinball tables including a mystery table based on one of [[PopCap Games|PopCap]]'s games.
*New trophies for all tables.
*New social system with in-game score notifications, challenges, Facebook posting, ProScore (personal performance across all tables) and TeamScore (a combined score ranking players and their friends).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesradar.com/zen-pinball-2-review/|title=Zen Pinball 2: Avengers Chronicles DLC review|author=Lucas Sullivan|date=19 June 2012|work=GamesRadar+|accessdate=9 August 2015}}</ref>
*New rule sheets to help a player better understand the tables, while still providing opportunity for players to discover the secrets of the table on their own.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kigyossy|first=Zsolt|title=Zen Pinball 2 Scores on PS3, Vita September 4th With PopCap Table|url=http://blog.us.playstation.com/2012/08/08/zen-pinball-2-scores-on-ps3-vita-september-4th-with-popcap-table/}}</ref>

